sentences: Evan Bogart (born January 23, 1978), better known as E. Kidd Bogart, is an American songwriter, music publisher, record executive and television producer.
Bogart's music has been nominated for three Grammy Awards, winning one, and he currently serves at President of the Los Angeles Chapter of The Recording Academy.
